Annotation.String: Performs validation checks on a purchase requisition
Performs validation checks on a purchase requisition using the purchase requisition number provided, and returns errors, if any.
Transitions external processing status of purchase requisition items, and enables them for purchasing

Transitions external processing status of purchase requisition items, and enables them for purchasing using the purchase requisition number and item number provided. If the item number is '00000', then the action is applied on all the items in the purchase requisition. This operation can only be applied on purchase requisition items with external processing status as In Process Externally.
Transitions external processing status of purchase requisition items, and discards them from purchasing

Transitions external processing status of purchase requisition items, and discards them from purchasing using the purchase requisition number and item number provided. If the item number is '00000', then the action is applied on all the items in the purchase requisition. This operation can only be applied on purchase requisition items with external processing status as In Process Externally.

PropertyValue.String: Creates a purchase requisition with one or more items

Creates a purchase requisition with one or more items. If "PurReqnDoOnlyValidation" is set to "True", it simulates the creation of a purchase requisition, and validates the correctness of the payload. In case the validation fails, it returns the errors in the response.
Updates the header details of a purchase requisition
Updates the header details of a purchase requisition using the purchase requisition number provided.
Adds an item to a purchase requisition
Adds an item to a purchase requisition using the purchase requisition number provided. It is mandatory to pass the purchase requisition number, " PurchaseRequisition", in the request body.
Updates the item details of an item in a purchase requisition
Updates the item details of an item in a purchase requisition, using the purchase requisition number, and item number provided.
Adds a new accounting line to an item in a purchase requisition

Adds a new accounting line to an item in a purchase requisition using the purchase requisition number, and item number provided. It is mandatory to provide the purchase requisition number, "PurchaseRequisition", and item number,"PurchaseRequisitionItem", in the request body. This operation is only supported as a batch request. Please note that while you add a new accounting line to an item, you must also correspondingly update the accounting details in the purchase requisition item, hence this operation is only supported as a batch request.
